# Conventional Commits

All git commit messages MUST follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
type(scope): subject
```

## Types

- `feat` — new feature
- `fix` — bug fix
- `refactor` — code change without feature/fix
- `chore` — tooling, deps, config
- `docs` — documentation only
- `style` — formatting, no logic change
- `test` — tests
- `build` — build system
- `ci` — CI config
- `perf` — performance
- `revert` — revert commit

## Rules

- Subject in **lowercase**, imperative mood, no trailing period
- Max **100 characters** in header
- Optional body after blank line for details
- Scope is optional but recommended (`ui`, `player`, `i18n`, `deps`)

## Examples

```
feat(ui): add genre cards on home page
fix(profile): stop infinite scroll on favorite stations
refactor(ui): migrate from chakra to shadcn
chore(deps): add biome and commitlint
```

## Do NOT

- Long prose summaries from change lists
- `Changes: 5f 100+30-` format
- Sentences like "Refactor project structure and update dependencies..."

When the user asks to commit, draft a conventional message and run `git commit` with it.

Note: Cursor Source Control "Generate commit message" (✨) reads `.cursorrules` at repo root, not this file. Keep both in sync.
